Cleopatra, Queen of Egypt, supported Antonius with her whole fleet and treasure at the battle of Actium, 31 B.c. Her flight led to the complete defeat of Antonius, who followed her to Alexandria, and, being pursued by the victorious Octavianus (Augustus Caesar), committed suicide there. Shortly afterwards Cleopatra, finding that she had no mercy to hope for from Octavianus, also com· mitted suicide—by allowing an asp to bite her, it was said, 30 B.c. These events assign this Ode to the same year.
